\f0\fs28 \cf0 To use an SDK for the API you are trying to integrate, there needs to be an SDK for the programming language you are using, and it needs to be well built. If there is no official SDK, you can search around and to find an unofficial one. \
If you find one, often that can still suffer from not being particularly good, especially as abandonment is a big problem in open-source. If the SDK is outdated, it\'92s potentially useless, and might be missing methods for the resources and endpoints your application might require.\
To ensure the SDK is of good quality, check for a few things.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li720\fi-500\sl288\slmult1\sb160\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
